# Install Terminator (shell)
```console
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:gnome-terminator
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install terminator
```
# Install guake Terminal
```console
sudo apt-get install guake
```
# Save original .dotfiles
```console
cd
mkdir -p ~/Downloads/MyBackups
mv .* ~/Downloads/MyBackups
```
# My dotfiles
```console
cd ~/Public
git clone https://github.com/julianobarbosa/dotfiles.git
```
# Link my dotfiles
```console
ln -s ~/Public/dotfiles/.zshrc ~
ln -s ~/Public/dotfiles/.weechat ~
ln -s ~/Public/dotfiles/.vimrc ~
ln -s ~/Public/dotfiles/.vimrc.local ~
ln -s ~/Public/dotfiles/.tmuxinator ~
ln -s ~/Public/dotfiles/.tmux ~
ln -s ~/Public/dotfiles/.tmux.conf ~
ln -s ~/Public/dotfiles/.screenrc ~
ln -s ~/Public/dotfiles/.my.cnf ~
ln -s ~/Public/dotfiles/.git ~
ln -s ~/Public/dotfiles/.gitconfig ~
```
# TMUX Plugin Install

```console
git clone https://github.com/tmux-plugins/tpm ~/.tmux/plugins/tpm
```

### Install powerline font
```bash
cd
wget https://github.com/powerline/powerline/raw/develop/font/PowerlineSymbols.otf
wget https://github.com/powerline/powerline/raw/develop/font/10-powerline-symbols.conf
mkdir -p ~/.config
mv PowerlineSymbols.otf ~/.fonts/
mkdir -p .config/fontconfig/conf.d 
mv 10-powerline-symbols.conf ~/.config/fontconfig/conf.d/
```

### Clean fonts cache
```console
fc-cache -vf ~/.fonts/
```

#### Change theme colors to solarize
```console
mkdir -p ~/.solarized
git clone git://github.com/sigurdga/gnome-terminal-colors-solarized.git ~/.solarized
cd ~/.solarized
./install.sh
```

# Install Telegram

### Download Program
https://desktop.telegram.org/

### uncompress
```console
xz -d tsetup*xz
tar xvf tsetup*
sudo mv Telegram /opt
```


## Install Whatsapp


# Google Drive

### Add Repository
```console
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:nilarimogard/webupd8
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install grive
```

# Install Keepass

### Add Repository
```console
sudo apt-add-repository ppa:jtaylor/keepass
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install keepass2
```
### Using Google Drive
```console
mkdir -p ~/grive
cd ~/grive
grive -a
```

### For more options 
```console
grive -h
```


